132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 709
H.P. 448 House of Representatives, February 25, 2025
An Act to Establish the Respite for ME Program
Submitted by the Department of Health and Human Services pursuant to Joint Rule 204.
Received by the Clerk of the House on February 20, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Health and Human Services pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed pursuant to Joint
Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative CLOUTIER of Lewiston.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 22 MRSA §7308, as amended by PL 2001, c. 487, §1, is repealed and the
3 following enacted in its place:
4 §7308. Respite for ME Program
5 The Respite for ME Program is established in the department. The department shall
6 administer the Respite for ME Program for the purpose of providing respite care, as
7 described in the federal Older Americans Act of 1965, 42 United States Code, Section
8 3030s-1(b)(4), and supplemental services, as described in 42 United States Code, Section
9 3030s-1(b)(5), for family caregivers as defined in 42 United States Code, Section 3022(3)
10 and older relative caregivers as defined in 42 United States Code, Section 3030s(a)(4).
11 SUMMARY
1122 This bill repeals the law that directs the Department of Health and Human Services to
1133 administer the Respite Care Fund and instead establishes the Respite for ME Program and
1144 directs the department to administer the Respite for ME Program for the purpose of
1155 providing respite care and supplemental services for family caregivers and older relative
1166 caregivers.
